node.text: We've made it to Ottawa for the holidays. Honey loves the snow and squirrels, Melly's meeting the whole family, and I'm loving wool socks by a fire, more food than I can handle, and no storms to worry about.
Next episode features hundreds of tiny engine parts and me checking off a bucket list item.

Working space is limited, so when something big needs time to bend and dry I'm pretty limited in my options. Here's the mast collar and adjoining bulkhead being slowly bent into shape while the epoxy cures.
Was hosted on this beautiful century old tall ship this weekend. Hosting is part of boat culture and I'm excited for the day I can proudly host others aboard old dog.
To whoever's sent out the goggles off the wishlist. Thank you so much! Canada post swallowed the packing slip so I have no idea where it came from. Honey loves em so long as we're moving quick.
Got a roll back from the Iceland trip. A few long haired beauties in these pics. Loved seeing the smile this brought to Melly's face.

I dont know how it came to be that I stumbled into Melly's world but I'm sure glad I did. I don't understand her style, half the languages she speaks, a good chunk of her cultural references, and how it is she picks the things she obsesses over, but I'm sure glad I'm one of those things. The tesla was dope, I definitely want that control screen in my life.

Sunshine is basically gone. Gotta get some wind turbines now, because the solar fun is over. For those of ya that wanna know the difference: average sunny day I'm making 2000watts right now. Average rainy day I'm making 200 watts. Hard to heat my tea on that.
Been driving the bug a bit this week. It's been a hectic week but honey loves our rides in the bug
Caught my first ever fish today. It's awesome the size of these monsters that live just around the corner from my place. Mine is the smallest, at 17lbs though this lingcod is no joke.

Flash back from last winter. Finally got some real old rolls of film developed. It's like Christmas getting a roll this old back. Melly really shines in these, and it definitely captures how our late night city life feels to me, such a world on contrast from my life on the boat out on a little island.
Back out to the boat and Honey's stoked. Videos being filmed now, works being done, but we gotta celebrate a bit first.
Flashback to the start of the spring season and the amazing hardworking of this crew, putting this whole underside together. Amazing amounts of work done in just two weeks.
A vacation in Germany, some castles, lots of wine and beer and bratwurst and sauerkraut, I wore a tie, went to a wedding, met the family and all together had an awesome vacation.

Iceland is done. The whale has done her job. It's been an awesome adventure, dipping my toe back into vanlife, I've loved the refresher, the break from boat work and the feeling of freedom. Thanks @kukucampers
The travel vlogger in his natural habitat
Hot water, cold weather.
Hope y'all ain't sick of waterfalls yet.
It was amazing to reset and see the world a little. Reminds me why I'm working so hard on this boat.
The dark castles. I feel like every place I go has a hole in a wall. I still always go though.
Expensive, crowded, luke warm, worth every damn penny. Check this cutey out oh man
Hey @kukucampers Iceland was dope. Thanks for making it affordable enough for a broke kid like me to see this country.

Iceland used to be really big on giant bluff bow oaken ships. They also dont have trees. These two facts seem to contradict, just like absolute shit climate of the land called Iceland, and the fragile ecosystem required for happy human existence. As an expert in self torture, I'm upset at how relatable this all is.
Spent a considerable amount of time just hanging around these hair metal rockers.
A taste of the #Vanlife for a week in an exotic climate and beautiful landscape. I'm so happy to be able to share this adventure with Melly this time.
